xt":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":17203,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/12\/16\/shurayh-praise-four-times\/","url_meta":{"origin":37285,"position":1},"title":"Shurayh on Calamity: I praise Allah four times if I am afflicted","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 16, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Sha\u2019bi reported: Shurayh, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cVerily, if I am afflicted by a calamity, then I praise Allah four times. I praise Him that it was not worse than it was. I praise Him as He provides me with the patience to bear it. I praise\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33106,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/08\/05\/first-thing-prophet-does\/","url_meta":{"origin":37285,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Siwak: First thing the Prophet does at home","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 5, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Shurayh reported: I asked Aisha, saying, \u201cWhat was the first thing the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, did when he entered his house?\u201d Aisha said, \u201cUse the toothstick.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 253 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Muslim \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0634\u064f\u0631\u064e\u064a\u0652\u062d\u064d \u0633\u064e\u0623\u064e\u0644\u0652\u062a\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0627\u0626\u0650\u0634\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0642\u064f\u0644\u0652\u062a\u064f \u0628\u0650\u0623\u064e\u064a\u0651\u0650 \u0634\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0621\u064d \u0643\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e \u064a\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u064e\u0623\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0651\u064f\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":5477,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/22\/umar-impressed-by-justice-shuraih\/","url_meta":{"origin":37285,"position":3},"title":"Umar on Justice: Judge Shurayh rules against the Caliph","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 22, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Sha\u2019bi reported: Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, took a horse from a man to test-ride it. The man handed it over and the horse injured its leg while it was with Umar. The man argued with him, so Umar said, \u201cLet a man judge between us.\u201d\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":6628,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/09\/18\/honor-his-guests\/","url_meta":{"origin":37285,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Hospitality: Let him honor his guests, speak goodness","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 18, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Shurayh reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever believes in Allah and the Last Day, let him honor his neighbor. Whoever\u00a0believes in Allah and the Last Day, let him\u00a0honor his guest and recompense him.\u201d They said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, what is his\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":40000,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2023\/05\/11\/overstay-welcome\/","url_meta":{"origin":37285,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Guests: Warning not to overstay your welcome","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 11, 2023","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Shurayh reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cHospitality for the guest is no more than three days, and it is courteous to host for one day and night. It is not lawful for a Muslim man to reside with his brother until he tempts him\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/37285","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=37285"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/37285\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/